---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Privacy Policy — vectorspace exchange">

  <main class="pt-32 pb-20 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto prose prose-invert prose-gray">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-2">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-gray-400 mb-10">Last updated: March 6, 2026</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-10 mb-3">1. Overview</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">
        VectorSpace Exchange ("we", "us", "our") operates the vectorspace.exchange website and API. This policy describes what data we collect, why we collect it, and how we handle it.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-10 mb-3">2. Our privacy-first approach</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">
        Our ad exchange is designed around privacy by default. We match ads to the current user intent, not to browsing history or user profiles. We do not use tracking cookies, fingerprinting, or cross-site tracking of any kind.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-10 mb-3">3. Data we collect</h2>
      <h3 class="text-lg font-medium mt-6 mb-2">3a. Ad requests (from publisher apps)</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">
        When a publisher app makes an ad request, we receive the intent string describing the user's current context. This string is used only for the duration of the auction to find a relevant ad. We do not store raw intent strings beyond short-term auction logs used for billing and fraud prevention.
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-lg font-medium mt-6 mb-2">3b. Intake form submissions</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">
        When you submit the publisher or advertiser intake form, we store your name, email, company/app name, and any details you provide. We use this information solely to evaluate your application and contact you about our service.
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-lg font-medium mt-6 mb-2">3c. Advertiser and publisher accounts</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">
        Registered advertisers and publishers provide account information (name, email, company) and configuration data (ad intent descriptions, bid prices, budgets). This data is used to operate the ad exchange.
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-lg font-medium mt-6 mb-2">3d. Event data</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">
        We record impression, click, and viewable events for billing, frequency capping, and reporting. Event records include the auction ID, advertiser ID, and an optional user ID provided by the publisher. We do not independently identify end users.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-10 mb-3">4. Data sharing</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">
        We do not sell personal data. We share aggregated, non-identifying auction statistics with publishers and advertisers through their respective dashboards. We may disclose data if required by law.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-10 mb-3">5. Data retention</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">
        Auction logs and event data are retained for up to 12 months for billing and reporting purposes. Intake form submissions are retained until your application is processed. Account data is retained as long as your account is active.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-10 mb-3">6. Security</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">
        Data is transmitted over TLS. Our infrastructure runs on AWS with encrypted storage. We support optional Trusted Execution Environment (TEE) enclaves for ad requests that require additional privacy guarantees.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-10 mb-3">7. Your rights</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">
        You may request access to, correction of, or deletion of your personal data by contacting us at <a href="mailto:privacy@vectorspace.exchange" class="text-brand-400 hover:underline">privacy@vectorspace.exchange</a>.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-10 mb-3">8. Changes</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">
        We may update this policy from time to time. Material changes will be posted on this page with an updated date.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-10 mb-3">9. Contact</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">
        Questions about this policy? Email <a href="mailto:privacy@vectorspace.exchange" class="text-brand-400 hover:underline">privacy@vectorspace.exchange</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </main>

</Base>
